1
00:00:11,042 --> 00:00:14,000
[ominous music playing]

2
00:00:17,583 --> 00:00:22,750
THE EVIL LAWYER

3
00:00:22,917 --> 00:00:26,083
[echoing crackle]

4
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:28,417
[ominous music continues]

5
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:39,833
[music stops]

6
00:00:39,917 --> 00:00:41,208
The country is buzzing right now,

7
00:00:41,292 --> 00:00:43,375
after the party leader's daughter
exposed the truth

8
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:45,333
on the Ruam Thai Party's rebranding stage.

9
00:00:45,417 --> 00:00:49,000
…details of the body cover-up at
Ruam Thai Party's boat party.

10
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:52,208
…certain revelations regarding
Dr. Suwat Pathumdechasakul,

11
00:00:52,292 --> 00:00:54,750
the Minister of Agriculture
and Cooperatives.

12
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:57,375
- Hey, Dr. Suwat is getting away!
- [intense music playing]

13
00:00:57,458 --> 00:00:59,833
- [camera shutters clicking]
- [reporters] Dr. Suwat! Dr. Suwat!

14
00:00:59,917 --> 00:01:03,000
- Dr. Suwat!
- Dr. Suwat, a word, please!

15
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:05,458
- [reporters] Dr. Suwat!
- [panting]

16
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:10,500
[reporter 1] General Anan is here!

17
00:01:10,583 --> 00:01:12,083
[reporters] General Anan!

18
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:14,667
- [camera shutters clicking]
- General, are the allegations true?

19
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:16,542
General, please answer us! General!

20
00:01:16,625 --> 00:01:18,083
General Anan!

21
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:20,542
[reporter 2] A word, please, sir.

22
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:22,208
[van door closes]

23
00:01:24,542 --> 00:01:25,667
Yes?

24
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:28,208
The party has no official statement yet.

25
00:01:28,292 --> 00:01:30,292
We'll contact you
as soon as we have one.

26
00:01:30,375 --> 00:01:31,750
- [phone ringing]
- Okay. Goodbye.

27
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:33,917
Yes, the party is discussing it right now.

28
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,375
We'll get back to you ASAP.

29
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:36,875
- Hello.
- I'm really sorry.

30
00:01:36,958 --> 00:01:38,542
[music falls]

31
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,083
[music fades]

32
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:44,667
If you can't control your own daughter,

33
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:46,667
how is our party supposed to function?

34
00:01:48,625 --> 00:01:50,667
[politician 1] How will you take
responsibility?

35
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:53,708
At the very least,
you should step down as the party leader.

36
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:01,167
I know you're all anxious right now.

37
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:03,833
But if we act out of impulse,

38
00:02:03,917 --> 00:02:05,958
it will only damage the party.

39
00:02:06,792 --> 00:02:09,542
I need everyone to stay calm.

40
00:02:11,292 --> 00:02:12,583
[politician 2] If I may.

41
00:02:13,917 --> 00:02:17,708
Per the party's resolution,
we all agree that

42
00:02:17,792 --> 00:02:19,833
what Ang said isn't true.

43
00:02:20,583 --> 00:02:24,125
It's a political smear campaign
orchestrated by our opponents.

44
00:02:24,958 --> 00:02:27,833
Please take care of this matter properly.

45
00:02:27,917 --> 00:02:30,458
[soft tense music playing]

46
00:02:33,583 --> 00:02:36,500
PRESS RELEASE: SEYA, SURVIVOR
FROM THE HELL OF THAI FISHING BOATS

47
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:38,583
DEMANDS OF THE SURVIVOR

48
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:42,083
POLICE REPORT
LIST OF PEOPLE ON THE BOAT

49
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:43,917
[music fades]

50
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,583
[Ang] I'll go over
the petition with you again.

51
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:49,292
When you testify, just tell the truth.

52
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:53,042
Tell them you got separated
from your sisters at Chai's pier,

53
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:55,083
and she was sent to Anan's boat.

54
00:02:56,208 --> 00:02:57,292
[Seya] Okay.

55
00:02:57,375 --> 00:03:00,500
Don't be nervous around the reporters.
You don't have to answer them.

56
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:01,958
We'll handle them for you.

57
00:03:02,667 --> 00:03:03,792
Okay.

58
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:08,000
I already contacted Tah's show.
We're just waiting for his reply.

59
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:10,958
[Pang] Nuch, make ten copies.

60
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,375
Don't be afraid.

61
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:16,708
We have plenty of people behind us.

62
00:03:18,458 --> 00:03:19,875
I'm prepared for this.

63
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:23,375
I don't want anyone else
to go through what my sisters did.

64
00:03:25,292 --> 00:03:27,750
[staff member] Officers,
you can't just barge in here.

65
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,458
[ominous music playing]

66
00:03:33,875 --> 00:03:35,208
Everyone, please wait outside

67
00:03:35,292 --> 00:03:37,667
while our officers inspect the premises.

68
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,000
Hold on.

69
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:40,458
What are you searching for?

70
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:45,625
We received a report that
you're taking illegal foreign funds

71
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:49,333
and hiring undocumented migrant workers.

72
00:03:49,417 --> 00:03:52,125
[Pang] We're an independent NGO.
Our funding is completely legal.

73
00:03:52,208 --> 00:03:54,125
It's all fully traceable and auditable.

74
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,042
What about you? You got a permit?

75
00:04:00,167 --> 00:04:01,750
- [music fades]
- Here is his permit.

76
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:05,000
He entered legally and has all the papers.
What else do you want?

77
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:08,750
He may have entered legally

78
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:12,042
but working for an organization
that receives illegal funds

79
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:14,958
may still carry a legal penalty.

80
00:04:15,042 --> 00:04:16,333
- Search!
- [Pang] Hey!

81
00:04:16,417 --> 00:04:17,583
Don't touch those documents!

82
00:04:17,667 --> 00:04:19,833
- Back off! Move!
- Hey, stop it!

83
00:04:19,917 --> 00:04:21,417
- [officer] Step aside!
- Seya!

84
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,667
[officer] Chai's case isn't closed yet.
You wanna try me?

85
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:26,208
I can arrest you right now.

86
00:04:26,917 --> 00:04:29,167
- Stay still!
- [intense music playing]

87
00:04:30,958 --> 00:04:32,125
Sit!

88
00:04:33,292 --> 00:04:34,375
Sit!

89
00:04:37,083 --> 00:04:38,583
What are you looking at?

90
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,542
- [Pang] Let go!
- [officer] Check over there too!

91
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:42,250
- [Pang] Stop!
- [officer] Check everything!

92
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:43,250
[music fades]

93
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:46,292
[news anchor]<i> The daughter</i>
<i>of the Ruam Thai Party leader</i>

94
00:04:46,375 --> 00:04:48,917
<i>has come forward to expose party members</i>

95
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,958
<i>right in the middle of</i>
<i>their rebranding event.</i>

96
00:04:51,042 --> 00:04:52,667
<i>She stated that people within the party</i>

97
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,833
<i>- are involved in a murder cover-up.</i>
- Holy shit.

98
00:04:55,917 --> 00:05:00,417
Your girl just dropped a nuke.
That's wild. [chuckles]

99
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:03,833
If the girl who died on that boat
is the reason you went to the golf course,

100
00:05:03,917 --> 00:05:05,250
you should've told me.

101
00:05:07,667 --> 00:05:10,208
I didn't think it would help the case.

102
00:05:10,292 --> 00:05:12,042
Plus, it affects other people.

103
00:05:13,792 --> 00:05:16,250
I know you don't want your girl involved.

104
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:19,292
But if we can get the people
from that boat party to talk,

105
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:21,917
the dead girl on the boat
will link directly to Anan.

106
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,375
She was Anan's employee.

107
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:25,875
And with Nay Oo being a third party
in your case,

108
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,458
it'll carry a lot more weight.

109
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:31,708
But everyone on that boat works for Anan.
They won't talk.

110
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:38,292
What if I tell you I have something
that can make them talk?

111
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,917
[foreboding music playing]

112
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,958
What is it?

113
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:50,000
[brakes screech]

114
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:58,583
- [music fades]
- [indistinct chatter]

115
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,500
Seya.

116
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,083
They really went this far?

117
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:18,042
What about Pang?

118
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:20,625
She was taken in for questioning.

119
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:23,375
The accusations are completely baseless.

120
00:06:24,917 --> 00:06:28,042
The police seized all our documents
about the boat party.

121
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:30,750
We need to do something right now

122
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,375
or my mom's party
will definitely cover it up.

123
00:06:40,083 --> 00:06:41,042
[sniffles]

124
00:06:45,542 --> 00:06:46,875
And if you expose it,

125
00:06:46,958 --> 00:06:49,458
and it gets covered up anyway?
What will you do, Ang?

126
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:52,250
[sighs deeply]

127
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:56,042
[Mek] Do you have a backup plan
to protect yourself?

128
00:07:00,917 --> 00:07:02,458
You probably think I'm stupid,

129
00:07:03,792 --> 00:07:05,708
reckless, or whatever.

130
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:07,042
[sniffles]

131
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,958
But if I don't do this,

132
00:07:10,792 --> 00:07:13,208
it will haunt me for the rest of my life.

133
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:16,958
[soft sorrowful music playing]

134
00:07:17,042 --> 00:07:18,625
It's not that I'm not scared.

135
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,167
I'm absolutely terrified.

136
00:07:22,708 --> 00:07:24,583
[sobs softly]

137
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:28,917
My biggest fear is that what I said today

138
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,417
still wasn't loud enough.

139
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,250
And tomorrow, people will forget.

140
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:47,833
[Ang sobs softly, sniffles]

141
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,875
I have info
that will make your voice louder.

142
00:07:54,958 --> 00:07:56,250
[music fades]

143
00:07:57,667 --> 00:08:00,583
It'll force the people on the boat
to cooperate with you.

144
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,042
What is it?

145
00:08:12,917 --> 00:08:16,042
[tense music playing]

146
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:21,375
[tense music continues]

147
00:08:27,083 --> 00:08:28,458
ANG

148
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:35,708
[dial tone ringing]

149
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:41,875
[voicemail] <i>The number you have dialed--</i>

150
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:03,875
[music fades]

151
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:20,958
[Suwat] Do you realize
you're committing political suicide?

152
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:23,792
I know exactly what I'm doing.

153
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,833
That's why I wanted to meet you today.

154
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:30,750
Don't tell me you're backing down.

155
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:33,708
[chuckles]

156
00:09:33,792 --> 00:09:35,917
You should go talk to your mother first,

157
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,167
or you can forget about the next term.

158
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:42,833
The Ruam Thai Party is finished.
No one supports you anymore.

159
00:09:42,917 --> 00:09:45,500
[foreboding music playing]

160
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:48,125
You're really worried about this,
aren't you?

161
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:50,042
Is that why you're threatening me?

162
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:54,792
But if we pin the blame on someone else,

163
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,167
then you wouldn't
have to be worried, right?

164
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,500
[Suwat] What do you mean?

165
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:05,583
You have to admit
that the boat incident truly happened.

166
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:08,833
But it was all Anan's fault.

167
00:10:09,708 --> 00:10:11,792
I'm confident this will end quickly,

168
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:13,625
and it definitely won't affect you.

169
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,792
How dare you say something like that?

170
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:29,417
[Mek] The case of stealing infant corpses
to make <i>kuman.</i>

171
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,333
But behind all of this

172
00:10:31,417 --> 00:10:33,833
is a transnational
infant corpse trafficking ring

173
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,083
involving rescue workers, temples,

174
00:10:37,167 --> 00:10:39,292
and hospitals that sell aborted fetuses.

175
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:43,542
We have a list of brokers ready to export,
both from America and Europe.

176
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:46,250
They run it like an industry
with a systematic supply chain.

177
00:10:47,542 --> 00:10:49,750
Suwat owns all of these businesses.

178
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,542
If you use this evidence

179
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:54,083
to make him confess,
I think it could work.

180
00:10:56,042 --> 00:10:57,083
Where did you get these?

181
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,500
Jittri used to represent Suwat's shaman.

182
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:06,208
You want me to blackmail Suwat

183
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,542
to make him confess about the boat party?

184
00:11:10,542 --> 00:11:11,750
Just think about it.

185
00:11:18,417 --> 00:11:20,917
[music rises, turns tense]

186
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,417
[Ang] Concealing a death carries
a maximum one-year sentence,

187
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:27,542
but stealing baby corpses for export?

188
00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:31,417
That's a transnational crime.
It's punishable in many countries.

189
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:33,375
[Suwat] How did you get these?

190
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,333
You should think about
which path you want to take.

191
00:11:41,792 --> 00:11:42,917
[Suwat] You little bitch!

192
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:46,000
You and your mom are both going down!

193
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:48,000
You dare threaten me? Just fucking wait!

194
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,625
You'll fucking see!

195
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:50,958
[tense music continues]

196
00:11:51,042 --> 00:11:52,625
[cell phone buzzing]

197
00:11:57,292 --> 00:11:58,583
- Hello.
- [Suwat]<i> Anan.</i>

198
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:01,000
<i>That bitch Ang is getting out of hand.</i>

199
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:05,208
<i>She tried to blackmail me with</i>
<i>the info about the </i>kuman <i>from Jittri.</i>

200
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:08,167
It's good that you came to me first.

201
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:11,667
If she really got the data from Jittri,

202
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,375
I'll handle it.

203
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:14,958
[Suwat] <i>Good. Don't let them--</i>

204
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:18,708
[music concludes]

205
00:12:18,792 --> 00:12:22,792
[news theme music playing]

206
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:24,875
NEW DAY NEWS

207
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:27,333
It's time for the 8:00 a.m. news.

208
00:12:27,417 --> 00:12:28,542
Mr. Boonlue Sansin,

209
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:32,125
also known as Master Boonlue
of the Samian Samakki Center,

210
00:12:32,208 --> 00:12:34,750
was found dead
in the center this morning.

211
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,667
<i>Police believe it was a suicide.</i>

212
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:40,625
<i>It is suspected that he was performing</i>
<i>a black magic ritual</i>

213
00:12:40,708 --> 00:12:43,167
<i>and intentionally overdosed on narcotics,</i>

214
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:45,917
<i>which led to loss of consciousness</i>
<i>and the tragic outcome.</i>

215
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,542
As for the latest news

216
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:49,875
following the shocking revelation
about the cover-up

217
00:12:49,958 --> 00:12:53,417
of the Myanmar worker's death
at the Ruam Thai Party event,

218
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:57,125
Minister of Agriculture,
Dr. Suwat Pathumdechasakul,

219
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:59,458
has just issued a statement to the press.

220
00:12:59,542 --> 00:13:02,458
For the daughter
of the Ruam Thai Party's leader

221
00:13:02,542 --> 00:13:04,583
to attack us without any evidence,

222
00:13:04,667 --> 00:13:05,917
[somber music playing]

223
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,083
I'm not entirely sure

224
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:10,417
if this is just a political game

225
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,000
since she recently resigned from the party

226
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,542
and joined forces with NGOs.

227
00:13:15,625 --> 00:13:20,250
<i>These groups are always ready</i>
<i>to attack us with fabricated lies.</i>

228
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:24,042
[music turns tense]

229
00:13:24,667 --> 00:13:26,375
[Atchara] Members of the press,

230
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:28,333
I am Dr. Atchara Thumnart,

231
00:13:28,417 --> 00:13:32,292
a party-list MP for the Ruam Thai Party,

232
00:13:32,375 --> 00:13:35,292
a party that has stood by the people
for over 20 years.

233
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:39,417
What I am about to tell you today
is the absolute truth

234
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:43,125
that my daughter,
Ms. Angsumalin, left unsaid.

235
00:13:43,958 --> 00:13:45,000
Is this for real?

236
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:46,708
- What?
- Is this true?

237
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:48,458
[reporter] What is it?

238
00:13:48,542 --> 00:13:50,542
[Ang] You have to resign from the party.

239
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:52,833
You came just to tell me this?

240
00:13:52,917 --> 00:13:54,000
[music concludes]

241
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:57,958
I'm sorry for putting you
in this predicament.

242
00:13:58,042 --> 00:14:00,333
But I won't apologize for speaking out.

243
00:14:00,417 --> 00:14:01,792
Because I've thought this through.

244
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:04,500
You disappeared for a whole week,

245
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:07,250
just to show up and tell me to resign?

246
00:14:07,917 --> 00:14:09,417
That's your well-thought plan?

247
00:14:09,958 --> 00:14:12,417
- [Ang] And you'll just let--
- Do you know how dangerous this is?

248
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,792
Do you have any idea?

249
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:16,583
You only dared to go this far--

250
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,125
You can't deny it.

251
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:20,792
It's because your mother
is the party leader.

252
00:14:20,875 --> 00:14:23,958
And now you want me to resign?

253
00:14:24,042 --> 00:14:27,542
What's the guarantee we'll be safe?

254
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:29,458
They're going to force you out anyway.

255
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:40,375
I'm not asking you to be a hero.

256
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:43,208
But this is your only way out.

257
00:14:45,542 --> 00:14:48,417
If you stay quiet, you're finished anyway.

258
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,667
[soft melancholic music playing]

259
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,083
[Ang sighs]

260
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,542
But if you choose to fight with me…

261
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:03,708
you'll still have a chance.

262
00:15:05,708 --> 00:15:07,458
At least, in the next election.

263
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:21,417
[music turns tense]

264
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:24,750
As the Fisheries Act goes to a vote
for its second reading,

265
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:26,583
a girl had to die

266
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,917
because of this slavery bill.

267
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,917
- [music rises]
- [reporters murmuring]

268
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:36,042
This bill benefits
the fishing export industry

269
00:15:36,125 --> 00:15:38,333
by creating loopholes
for human trafficking,

270
00:15:38,417 --> 00:15:40,583
making it easier
to exploit labor on ships.

271
00:15:40,667 --> 00:15:45,125
My daughter, Ang,
wanted to fix this loophole.

272
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:47,917
But a covered-up murder case
put her in a difficult position.

273
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,083
I have a list of everyone involved

274
00:15:50,167 --> 00:15:52,417
in the cover-up of Ms. Nee An's death,

275
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:55,167
the waitress who died
on Police General Anan's boat.

276
00:15:56,042 --> 00:15:58,833
And as a representative
of the Ruam Thai Party,

277
00:15:58,917 --> 00:16:02,750
if I cannot reveal the whole truth
to the people,

278
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,917
I will take responsibility by resigning.

279
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,917
[camera shutters clicking]

280
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,667
- [music rises]
- [reporters clamoring]

281
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:13,792
Sir, did she consult you beforehand?

282
00:16:14,583 --> 00:16:15,708
Sir.

283
00:16:15,792 --> 00:16:20,708
[reporters clamoring]

284
00:16:20,792 --> 00:16:22,083
[music falls]

285
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:24,583
[Anan] They don't have
enough evidence against us.

286
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:27,417
Panicking just plays into their hands.

287
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:30,292
Just stay put. I'll handle it.

288
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:31,917
[sighs]

289
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,542
[music rises]

290
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:51,708
[music builds]

291
00:16:51,792 --> 00:16:54,542
[music concludes]

292
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,958
[in English] What are you doing here?

293
00:16:59,042 --> 00:17:00,875
[Andy] Sorry for showing up unannounced.

294
00:17:00,958 --> 00:17:03,792
But your father-in-law
has graciously welcomed me.

295
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:05,792
[foreboding music playing]

296
00:17:08,625 --> 00:17:09,917
We shouldn't talk here.

297
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,250
You can talk here.

298
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:13,417
Sit down.

299
00:17:16,125 --> 00:17:17,833
[sighs]

300
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:21,417
[breathes deeply]

301
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:25,625
[sighs]

302
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:31,042
I know we've got a lot of things to talk.

303
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:34,500
But I'm in a hurry. I've gotta go.

304
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:37,333
Why? What are you afraid of?

305
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:43,083
This is not the place to talk business.

306
00:17:43,167 --> 00:17:45,542
You mean the failing business?

307
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:51,750
We now have hundreds of
containers of trash stuck in Laem Chabang.

308
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:55,000
And you haven't even wrapped up
the factory fire case.

309
00:17:55,125 --> 00:17:56,875
Boss Zhou is getting impatient.

310
00:17:56,958 --> 00:17:58,458
[exhales sharply]

311
00:18:00,375 --> 00:18:02,792
I'm not worried. Why would you?

312
00:18:02,875 --> 00:18:04,292
Really?

313
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:08,708
If you're not worried,
why kill your own right-hand man?

314
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:12,542
[in Thai] Chai.

315
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:15,833
[in English] Did I say his name correctly?

316
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,625
You can't even solve your own son's death

317
00:18:19,917 --> 00:18:22,250
but this is the case of living people.

318
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,458
Settle this case right now.

319
00:18:24,542 --> 00:18:27,000
Boss Zhou doesn't want to waste
his money on this anymore.

320
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,042
Are you done?

321
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:36,250
I respect you.
That's why I'm talking to you.

322
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:39,167
Otherwise, I'll be talking to your bosses.

323
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:42,167
Right, Uncle?

324
00:18:53,417 --> 00:18:55,458
Your men here are really good-looking.

325
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:58,750
Maybe you should send one of them to me.

326
00:19:04,542 --> 00:19:06,750
[door opens, closes]

327
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:13,167
[exhales deeply]

328
00:19:13,792 --> 00:19:15,292
[in Thai] I'll handle it, Dad.

329
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:18,875
[breathes deeply]

330
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:22,208
[tense dramatic music playing]

331
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:30,542
[Anan] <i>On March 12, 2026,</i>

332
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:32,958
at approximately 9:00 a.m.,

333
00:19:33,042 --> 00:19:35,417
the Anti Human Trafficking Division

334
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:40,167
<i>raided a restaurant in Huai Khwang.</i>

335
00:19:44,875 --> 00:19:46,917
- [commando] Nobody move!
- [staff clamoring]

336
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,792
[commando] Hands behind your back!
Right Now!

337
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:53,000
[Anan]<i> We arrested Mr. Andy Luochen Tian,</i>

338
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:57,542
<i>the owner of the illegal</i>
<i>imported recycling factory network.</i>

339
00:19:57,625 --> 00:20:01,958
One of them was the
Rungruang E-Waste Recycling Factory,

340
00:20:02,042 --> 00:20:04,792
which caught on fire recently.

341
00:20:04,875 --> 00:20:08,750
<i>Mr. Andy will be extradited</i>
<i>to face trial in his home country,</i>

342
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,417
<i>to maintain good international relations.</i>

343
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,125
[in English] Hey! What the fuck?!

344
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,292
Motherfucker.

345
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:20,167
[in Thai] I must reiterate
once again that…

346
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:23,000
these people,

347
00:20:23,792 --> 00:20:26,333
without the cooperation of Thais,

348
00:20:26,417 --> 00:20:28,583
couldn't run a business like this.

349
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:34,167
They build relationships
with political groups.

350
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:38,000
- [reporters murmuring]
- [Anan] They exploit legislation

351
00:20:38,083 --> 00:20:40,917
to benefit their own cronies.

352
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,375
LABOR TRAFFICKING CRACKDOWN

353
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:44,542
<i>I will take strict legal action</i>

354
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:47,583
<i>against everyone involved.</i>

355
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:50,333
[reporter 1] Ms. Atchara, are you worried
about being questioned?

356
00:20:50,417 --> 00:20:51,542
Please answer us.

357
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:54,000
[reporter 2]<i> Before his death,</i>

358
00:20:54,083 --> 00:20:57,458
<i>your son, Techin, represented</i>
<i>the waste plant owners.</i>

359
00:20:57,542 --> 00:21:00,958
<i>Do you feel any pressure</i>
<i>handling this case, Mr. Anan?</i>

360
00:21:02,292 --> 00:21:03,417
None at all.

361
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,458
I'm simply doing my duty.

362
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:10,375
As for my son's case…

363
00:21:11,708 --> 00:21:13,750
I believe in the justice system.

364
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:18,417
We must leave it up to the judge…

365
00:21:19,958 --> 00:21:24,292
and I trust they're doing
their absolute best right now.

366
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:30,083
OFFICE OF THE JUDICIARY

367
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:32,208
[music concludes]

368
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:39,625
I don't understand why Judge Rit
is stepping down from the chief position.

369
00:21:39,708 --> 00:21:43,667
That's why I asked
both of you to come in today.

370
00:21:44,583 --> 00:21:46,667
Because if you step down,

371
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:51,750
I'll have to promote Judge Padung,
as he is next in line.

372
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:57,542
I am no longer qualified
to perform these duties.

373
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:04,208
Are you dealing with personal issues,
Judge Rit?

374
00:22:09,708 --> 00:22:11,250
The problem is…

375
00:22:12,667 --> 00:22:15,000
I took a bribe in the waste plant case.

376
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:17,458
[foreboding music playing]

377
00:22:17,542 --> 00:22:22,000
I am too ashamed to continue in this role.

378
00:22:23,375 --> 00:22:24,458
[sighs]

379
00:22:25,458 --> 00:22:27,750
Can you explain what happened?

380
00:22:30,792 --> 00:22:34,333
Someone made me an offer
to close the waste plant case

381
00:22:35,708 --> 00:22:38,625
in exchange for
helping with my son's case.

382
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:43,583
[Padung] Sign off on the verdict

383
00:22:43,667 --> 00:22:45,917
for the waste plant case, please.

384
00:22:48,917 --> 00:22:51,958
- [in English] How much do you want?
- Fifty million.

385
00:22:52,917 --> 00:22:54,583
[whistles]

386
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:58,958
MR. RIT PIRIYAWICH, CO-JUDGE

387
00:23:01,208 --> 00:23:04,083
[in Thai] And don't you worry
about your son's case.

388
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:05,875
I'll take care of it.

389
00:23:08,125 --> 00:23:09,458
Thank you.

390
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:16,250
<i>Since he's in charge of that case file,</i>

391
00:23:17,417 --> 00:23:21,083
he guaranteed I wouldn't have to worry
about my son's case anymore.

392
00:23:23,083 --> 00:23:24,292
If I just…

393
00:23:25,292 --> 00:23:28,792
signed off on the waste plant case
like he wanted.

394
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:32,083
Wait, Judge Rit, what are you saying?

395
00:23:33,250 --> 00:23:34,458
How could that be true?

396
00:23:34,542 --> 00:23:36,750
Are you talking about Judge Padung?

397
00:23:39,917 --> 00:23:40,917
Yes.

398
00:23:42,417 --> 00:23:43,417
Here.

399
00:23:47,333 --> 00:23:49,583
I have complete evidence of everything.

400
00:23:50,250 --> 00:23:54,750
All my financial records
linking me to Judge Padung.

401
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,542
[breathes shakily]

402
00:23:56,625 --> 00:23:59,833
[committee member]
Do you realize that admitting this

403
00:24:00,500 --> 00:24:03,000
will not only get you fired
from government service

404
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:06,750
but also mean that the NACC
will prosecute you for corruption?

405
00:24:08,792 --> 00:24:09,958
I am fully aware.

406
00:24:11,875 --> 00:24:14,167
That is why both Judge Padung and I

407
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:18,958
are no longer fit to serve as judges.

408
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:21,542
[music intensifies]

409
00:24:29,833 --> 00:24:31,500
- Thank you.
- [music concludes]

410
00:24:33,167 --> 00:24:34,583
[Jittri] Good news.

411
00:24:34,667 --> 00:24:36,583
Mek's case has a new judge.

412
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:40,083
Your dad confessed to taking a bribe
from Padung in the factory fire case.

413
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:41,542
So they both got dismissed.

414
00:24:42,458 --> 00:24:44,500
Noi, call Dr. Korn.

415
00:24:44,583 --> 00:24:46,250
We need to hurry and add another witness.

416
00:24:46,333 --> 00:24:47,292
[Noi] Got it.

417
00:24:48,375 --> 00:24:50,125
[Kung] Mek, I have a serious question.

418
00:24:51,083 --> 00:24:53,042
Have you ordained for your dad yet?

419
00:24:53,583 --> 00:24:55,375
- What, man?
- [Kung] Damn you!

420
00:24:55,458 --> 00:24:58,583
He did so much for you.
You should repay him.

421
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:00,583
Just go all out and do eight years.

422
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:03,333
Let him ride your robes
to heaven, bastard.

423
00:25:05,375 --> 00:25:07,792
So at the next hearing,
the only evidence we have left to prove

424
00:25:07,875 --> 00:25:10,083
is my bone was broken
and I couldn't hit Techin.

425
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,833
Right. As for Anan,

426
00:25:11,917 --> 00:25:14,167
if he's willing to sacrifice
his own investors,

427
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:16,208
it means this is his only way out.

428
00:25:17,625 --> 00:25:20,292
Hey, the news is blowing up right now.

429
00:25:20,375 --> 00:25:21,958
They're saying you wanted to kill Techin

430
00:25:22,042 --> 00:25:25,125
to cover up the factory fire
for the Ruam Thai Party.

431
00:25:25,208 --> 00:25:27,292
Plus, you're fooling around
with the leader's daughter

432
00:25:27,375 --> 00:25:28,875
to frame Anan.

433
00:25:28,958 --> 00:25:29,958
Oh…

434
00:25:30,042 --> 00:25:32,958
Fuck! Are they writing the news
or a Webtoon plot?

435
00:25:33,792 --> 00:25:36,875
Dr. Korn's wife says
he'll withdraw as a witness.

436
00:25:36,958 --> 00:25:39,583
- What?
- [Kung] I knew it.

437
00:25:39,667 --> 00:25:41,625
The doctor's wife is so damn thin-skinned.

438
00:25:41,708 --> 00:25:45,000
If news suddenly breaks that her husband
helped a dirty-money murderer,

439
00:25:45,083 --> 00:25:46,792
she'd scream to death, man.

440
00:25:50,083 --> 00:25:51,833
[clicks tongue] Damn it!

441
00:25:52,625 --> 00:25:54,750
And we already managed
to change the judge.

442
00:25:55,542 --> 00:25:57,042
We got that asshole Padung out,

443
00:25:57,125 --> 00:25:58,750
and now Dr. Korn bails too. Fuck!

444
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:01,792
With him gone, we can't prove
you were actually hurt.

445
00:26:01,875 --> 00:26:05,083
You walking into court now
is like walking into prison.

446
00:26:07,375 --> 00:26:11,125
[Jittri] We have to find a way to prove
that a third person was there.

447
00:26:11,208 --> 00:26:13,250
We have Nay Oo's DNA on the bracelet.

448
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:15,083
We'll use this to fight in court.

449
00:26:15,917 --> 00:26:17,625
If evidence suddenly pops up like this,

450
00:26:17,708 --> 00:26:20,042
with no witness or anything at all,
won't it get dismissed?

451
00:26:20,125 --> 00:26:21,458
I really don't know.

452
00:26:21,542 --> 00:26:24,042
We'll have to see
if the new judge accepts it.

453
00:26:24,125 --> 00:26:27,833
This is all the time we have.
We can't do much more than this.

454
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:32,583
[sighs, clicks tongue]

455
00:26:40,375 --> 00:26:43,583
DIRTY-MONEY LAWYER PLANS
TO SILENCE POLICE OFFICER'S SON

456
00:26:43,667 --> 00:26:45,875
[soft suspenseful music playing]

457
00:27:11,167 --> 00:27:12,333
DECEASED

458
00:27:12,417 --> 00:27:14,375
DR. KORN
CONFIRMING THE INJURY

459
00:27:14,458 --> 00:27:16,333
19 SEPTEMBER 2025

460
00:27:16,417 --> 00:27:18,000
THREE MIGRANT WORKER SIBLINGS

461
00:27:18,083 --> 00:27:20,375
BANK TRANSFER RECORDS
ON THE DAY OF THE INCIDENT

462
00:27:22,958 --> 00:27:24,708
I think I have a way.

463
00:27:29,833 --> 00:27:30,958
[music concludes]

464
00:27:31,042 --> 00:27:33,417
DEFENSE WITNESS EXAMINATION:
GOLF COURSE CASE

465
00:27:40,375 --> 00:27:42,667
They brought reporters in this time.

466
00:27:42,750 --> 00:27:44,208
That's why it's so crowded.

467
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:48,458
I have no idea what trick
Attorney Jittri is going to pull.

468
00:27:52,458 --> 00:27:54,792
[tense music playing]

469
00:28:11,375 --> 00:28:15,000
PUBLIC GALLERY

470
00:28:33,833 --> 00:28:36,042
[music fades]

471
00:28:36,125 --> 00:28:41,917
This is the defense witness examination
for case O.927/2568.

472
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:44,958
Since this case has dragged on
long enough,

473
00:28:46,042 --> 00:28:49,375
I want the witness examination
to be as concise as possible,

474
00:28:49,458 --> 00:28:51,375
and it must conclude by today.

475
00:28:52,333 --> 00:28:54,167
Call the first witness.

476
00:28:56,375 --> 00:28:58,750
[tense music playing]

477
00:29:09,333 --> 00:29:11,167
The defense may examine the witness.

478
00:29:19,167 --> 00:29:21,625
- Are you ready?
- I'm ready.

479
00:29:21,708 --> 00:29:23,792
Please tell us what happened that night.

480
00:29:23,875 --> 00:29:25,417
[music fades]

481
00:29:26,125 --> 00:29:29,167
That night, I was patrolling as usual,

482
00:29:29,250 --> 00:29:31,667
along the golf course before Khao Yai.

483
00:29:34,208 --> 00:29:36,708
<i>- I heard two gunshots.</i>
- [gunshot]

484
00:29:36,792 --> 00:29:39,708
[Sorn]<i> So I parked</i>
<i>and ran toward the sound.</i>

485
00:29:40,667 --> 00:29:41,750
[gunshot]

486
00:29:41,833 --> 00:29:44,542
[mysterious music playing]

487
00:29:46,167 --> 00:29:48,917
[Sorn] <i>From a distance, I saw the guard</i>

488
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:51,750
<i>pinning the defendant near the body.</i>

489
00:29:52,875 --> 00:29:54,583
<i>But before reaching the scene,</i>

490
00:29:54,667 --> 00:29:58,375
<i>I saw a woman in a caddy uniform,</i>
<i>covered in blood, run into the woods.</i>

491
00:29:59,583 --> 00:30:03,000
<i>She had long hair and was holding a gun.</i>

492
00:30:03,083 --> 00:30:04,208
[prosecutor] <i>Hold on.</i>

493
00:30:04,292 --> 00:30:05,167
[music fades]

494
00:30:05,250 --> 00:30:08,708
Why wasn't this crucial detail
mentioned during the investigation?

495
00:30:08,792 --> 00:30:10,833
I told the police everything that day.

496
00:30:10,917 --> 00:30:12,875
But they said it was irrelevant,

497
00:30:12,958 --> 00:30:14,792
so it wasn't put on record.

498
00:30:16,083 --> 00:30:18,500
Are you accusing the police
of burying evidence?

499
00:30:18,583 --> 00:30:20,875
Do you really want to cross the police?

500
00:30:20,958 --> 00:30:22,333
[Jittri] Objection.

501
00:30:22,417 --> 00:30:24,583
The prosecutor is threatening the witness.

502
00:30:24,667 --> 00:30:26,500
[tense music playing]

503
00:30:26,583 --> 00:30:29,333
I apologize if it came across that way.

504
00:30:29,958 --> 00:30:32,042
I was merely stating a fact.

505
00:30:32,125 --> 00:30:35,750
Prosecutor, refrain from using threats.

506
00:30:35,833 --> 00:30:37,458
Call your next witness.

507
00:30:49,667 --> 00:30:51,417
Who is the person in the photo?

508
00:30:55,125 --> 00:30:58,125
[music concludes]

509
00:30:59,750 --> 00:31:01,375
I'm her younger brother.

510
00:31:02,833 --> 00:31:05,958
My sister attacked the victim that night.

511
00:31:06,042 --> 00:31:09,167
[water burbling]

512
00:31:09,250 --> 00:31:11,625
[insects trilling]

513
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:18,625
[suspenseful music playing]

514
00:31:23,708 --> 00:31:25,500
[Seya] My sister told me

515
00:31:25,583 --> 00:31:27,958
her boss was about to kill her.

516
00:31:29,042 --> 00:31:31,750
She only did it in self-defense.

517
00:31:31,833 --> 00:31:35,208
She grabbed the gun
because she feared he'd attack her again.

518
00:31:37,208 --> 00:31:38,625
[Jittri] Is this the gun?

519
00:31:39,667 --> 00:31:40,667
[Seya] Yes.

520
00:31:41,958 --> 00:31:45,083
It's the same one my sister hid.

521
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:49,583
When she vanished,
I used it to threaten Chai.

522
00:31:50,917 --> 00:31:53,292
Then he shot me with this very gun.

523
00:31:53,375 --> 00:31:55,958
[music intensifies]

524
00:31:57,542 --> 00:31:59,875
[forensic expert] <i>We tested</i>
<i>the DNA from the bloodstain,</i>

525
00:31:59,958 --> 00:32:03,333
<i>and the blood found on the gun, Exhibit 1,</i>

526
00:32:04,917 --> 00:32:07,167
contained Ms. Nay Oo's DNA.

527
00:32:07,250 --> 00:32:09,625
By comparing the DNA results

528
00:32:09,708 --> 00:32:12,375
with the bracelet, Exhibit 2,

529
00:32:12,458 --> 00:32:15,000
<i>we confirmed that Seya and Nay Oo</i>

530
00:32:15,083 --> 00:32:16,292
are biological siblings.

531
00:32:17,292 --> 00:32:20,542
- [music concludes]
- That gun was reported stolen.

532
00:32:20,625 --> 00:32:23,750
How do we know the blood
wasn't planted later?

533
00:32:25,375 --> 00:32:27,583
My job is strictly to test the evidence.

534
00:32:27,667 --> 00:32:31,250
I can't determine if the blood
was planted after the fact.

535
00:32:31,333 --> 00:32:35,000
So it's possible it was planted later.
Is that correct?

536
00:32:35,083 --> 00:32:37,667
[tense music playing]

537
00:32:38,708 --> 00:32:40,083
There's a possibility.

538
00:32:41,167 --> 00:32:43,500
And the only evidence we get
from DNA on the bracelet

539
00:32:43,583 --> 00:32:46,625
is that Ms. Nay Oo and Seya are related.

540
00:32:47,125 --> 00:32:48,625
But you cannot confirm

541
00:32:48,708 --> 00:32:50,833
that Ms. Nay Oo was the third party

542
00:32:50,917 --> 00:32:53,542
at the scene, as claimed. Is that right?

543
00:32:57,250 --> 00:32:58,417
That's correct.

544
00:32:59,667 --> 00:33:00,875
I can't confirm.

545
00:33:02,667 --> 00:33:04,542
[music concludes]

546
00:33:04,625 --> 00:33:06,333
[prosecutor] No further questions.

547
00:33:09,250 --> 00:33:10,958
[judge] If there are no other witnesses,

548
00:33:11,042 --> 00:33:12,583
the defendant may take the stand.

549
00:33:27,458 --> 00:33:28,625
I'm counting on you.

550
00:33:43,500 --> 00:33:44,875
[inhales deeply]

551
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:23,708
Counsel, you may examine the defendant.

552
00:34:31,625 --> 00:34:32,958
On the night of the incident,

553
00:34:33,042 --> 00:34:35,958
did you go to the victim's house?

554
00:34:36,042 --> 00:34:37,333
Please tell us what happened.

555
00:34:43,250 --> 00:34:44,292
Yes, I did.

556
00:34:44,917 --> 00:34:46,458
Techin asked me to come over.

557
00:34:47,833 --> 00:34:50,375
He said his dad ordered him
to do something important.

558
00:34:51,625 --> 00:34:53,583
He also said if I didn't help him…

559
00:34:55,458 --> 00:34:58,458
Ang, my ex-girlfriend,

560
00:34:58,542 --> 00:34:59,750
would be in trouble too.

561
00:35:02,625 --> 00:35:04,750
That night, Techin brought a new caddy.

562
00:35:04,833 --> 00:35:06,042
Her name was Nay Oo.

563
00:35:06,583 --> 00:35:09,708
She was a witness to the incident
on the Chaophraya boat,

564
00:35:09,792 --> 00:35:12,333
where they covered up Nee An's death.

565
00:35:12,417 --> 00:35:13,958
She's Nay Oo's younger sister.

566
00:35:14,042 --> 00:35:15,125
[soft tense music playing]

567
00:35:15,208 --> 00:35:17,333
Techin was afraid
the truth would come out,

568
00:35:18,417 --> 00:35:20,583
so he planned to silence Nay Oo.

569
00:35:23,208 --> 00:35:25,500
And I decided to help him.

570
00:35:25,583 --> 00:35:28,167
[music rises, darkens]

571
00:35:36,333 --> 00:35:37,375
[Nay Oo yelps]

572
00:35:42,750 --> 00:35:43,917
[Nay Oo groans]

573
00:35:46,250 --> 00:35:48,792
[Mek] <i>We took Nay Oo to the sand bunker.</i>

574
00:35:48,875 --> 00:35:50,500
<i>We planned to shoot her there.</i>

575
00:36:02,208 --> 00:36:03,792
<i>But in the end, Techin couldn't do it.</i>

576
00:36:03,875 --> 00:36:06,125
[somber music playing]

577
00:36:06,208 --> 00:36:09,458
[Mek] <i>He just stood there</i>
<i>blaming himself for failing his dad.</i>

578
00:36:09,542 --> 00:36:11,833
<i>So I decided to grab the gun.</i>

579
00:36:11,917 --> 00:36:12,958
I'll do it.

580
00:36:14,333 --> 00:36:15,500
- [Nay Oo screams]
- [grunts]

581
00:36:15,583 --> 00:36:18,667
<i>Nay Oo took the chance to grab a club</i>
<i>and hit me in the shoulder.</i>

582
00:36:18,750 --> 00:36:20,708
<i>- So Techin tried to help me.</i>
- [golf club clangs]

583
00:36:21,625 --> 00:36:25,000
[Mek]<i> When Techin went for the gun,</i>
<i>Nay Oo hit the back of his head.</i>

584
00:36:25,083 --> 00:36:26,375
[Nay Oo grunts, sobs]

585
00:36:26,458 --> 00:36:28,083
[screams]

586
00:36:29,583 --> 00:36:31,000
[sobs]

587
00:36:31,083 --> 00:36:32,250
[golf club thwacks]

588
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,875
[both panting]

589
00:36:37,250 --> 00:36:38,958
[Mek] <i>I tried to stop her.</i>

590
00:36:41,458 --> 00:36:42,792
<i>But it was too late.</i>

591
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:51,875
[music falls]

592
00:36:51,958 --> 00:36:53,125
I never thought--

593
00:36:53,208 --> 00:36:56,208
You tried to kill my sister? You bastard!

594
00:36:56,833 --> 00:36:58,792
[judge] Witness, please control yourself.

595
00:36:58,875 --> 00:36:59,958
[Ang] Seya.

596
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:03,917
[Mek breathes softly]

597
00:37:04,792 --> 00:37:07,250
Why did you agree to commit such a crime?

598
00:37:12,333 --> 00:37:14,708
Techin and I had been close since school.

599
00:37:18,208 --> 00:37:19,667
Even though he was my junior,

600
00:37:20,958 --> 00:37:22,875
we were like close friends.

601
00:37:24,125 --> 00:37:26,458
After graduation, we kept in touch.

602
00:37:27,958 --> 00:37:31,208
Like with the waste plant fire,
he also asked for my help.

603
00:37:32,917 --> 00:37:34,667
Do you have proof of this?

604
00:37:37,250 --> 00:37:39,500
I have proof of a 300,000-baht transfer

605
00:37:39,583 --> 00:37:42,000
that Techin sent me
on the day of the incident.

606
00:37:42,625 --> 00:37:46,000
He transferred it as a thank-you
for helping with the factory case.

607
00:37:46,083 --> 00:37:48,250
[soft tense music playing]

608
00:37:50,375 --> 00:37:52,208
But I didn't want the money.

609
00:37:52,292 --> 00:37:53,958
I just wanted to help him.

610
00:37:57,750 --> 00:37:59,375
I know it was wrong.

611
00:38:00,417 --> 00:38:02,958
But I couldn't help but pity him.

612
00:38:04,667 --> 00:38:08,000
Being pressured by his own father
to do something against his will.

613
00:38:16,625 --> 00:38:17,708
No further questions.

614
00:38:25,042 --> 00:38:27,167
[judge] The prosecution may cross-examine.

615
00:38:36,458 --> 00:38:38,833
[music fades]

616
00:38:39,625 --> 00:38:43,125
Why does your testimony differ
from your initial statement?

617
00:38:44,125 --> 00:38:46,125
There's no record of your injuries at all.

618
00:38:46,208 --> 00:38:47,750
[tense music resumes]

619
00:38:47,833 --> 00:38:51,542
The arresting officers
never asked about my wounds.

620
00:38:53,125 --> 00:38:55,375
They just rushed to lock me up.
Didn't ask a single thing.

621
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:56,833
You're a lawyer.

622
00:38:56,917 --> 00:38:58,417
You know exactly how to answer.

623
00:38:58,500 --> 00:39:00,667
And how to spin a story to save yourself.

624
00:39:00,750 --> 00:39:01,875
Am I right?

625
00:39:02,500 --> 00:39:04,333
Just answer yes or no.

626
00:39:06,375 --> 00:39:07,542
[music falls]

627
00:39:07,625 --> 00:39:09,708
[breathes shakily]

628
00:39:10,917 --> 00:39:12,125
Yes.

629
00:39:13,667 --> 00:39:15,417
You know the laws well.

630
00:39:15,500 --> 00:39:16,958
You already know, don't you,

631
00:39:17,042 --> 00:39:18,625
that a bribery charge

632
00:39:18,708 --> 00:39:21,792
carries a lighter sentence
than attempted murder?

633
00:39:21,875 --> 00:39:23,458
That's why you chose this story.

634
00:39:26,667 --> 00:39:29,083
You may think I'm not telling the truth,

635
00:39:29,167 --> 00:39:30,583
or even that I'm lying.

636
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,083
But this is the only truth I have.

637
00:39:53,208 --> 00:39:54,583
[prosecutor] No further questions.

638
00:39:54,667 --> 00:39:56,208
[music fades]

639
00:39:59,167 --> 00:40:01,250
Today's hearing is adjourned.

640
00:40:02,292 --> 00:40:05,583
The verdict will be read on April 2nd.

641
00:40:07,083 --> 00:40:10,000
[foreboding music playing]

642
00:40:20,917 --> 00:40:22,500
[Kung] Hey!

643
00:40:22,583 --> 00:40:24,417
- [in Burmese] You scumbag!
- [in Thai] Calm down!

644
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:26,083
[in Burmese] You tried to kill my sister?

645
00:40:26,167 --> 00:40:28,042
You bastard! You tried to kill my sister?!

646
00:40:28,125 --> 00:40:30,333
- [Ang] Seya!
- I'll kill you!

647
00:40:30,417 --> 00:40:31,917
[dark pensive music playing]

648
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,167
[Kung in Thai] This is
a courtroom, bastard!

649
00:40:37,167 --> 00:40:38,333
[Seya in Burmese] Bastard!

650
00:40:38,792 --> 00:40:40,250
[Kung in Thai] Are you okay?

651
00:40:41,958 --> 00:40:43,000
I'm fine.

652
00:40:44,417 --> 00:40:45,667
[Jittri] Don't follow me.

653
00:40:50,292 --> 00:40:52,417
- [door opens]
- Where am I supposed to be?

654
00:40:55,167 --> 00:40:56,625
I'll go wait outside.

655
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,167
[door opens]

656
00:41:13,875 --> 00:41:15,000
[door closes]

657
00:41:39,583 --> 00:41:41,208
[music fades]

658
00:41:42,458 --> 00:41:44,375
- [Ang] What is it?
- [Jittri] Let me talk to him.

659
00:41:44,458 --> 00:41:45,958
You can talk to me.

660
00:41:48,208 --> 00:41:49,667
I know you're angry.

661
00:41:50,833 --> 00:41:52,542
But you have to accept the truth

662
00:41:52,625 --> 00:41:54,417
that your sister might never come back.

663
00:41:55,750 --> 00:41:56,750
No.

664
00:41:57,792 --> 00:42:02,333
Until I know where Nay Oo is,
I won't stop looking.

665
00:42:05,458 --> 00:42:07,375
I'm not telling you to stop looking.

666
00:42:07,458 --> 00:42:09,833
[somber music playing]

667
00:42:10,792 --> 00:42:13,375
Because I never stopped looking
for my dad either.

668
00:42:36,125 --> 00:42:39,500
- [birds chirping]
- [music fades]

669
00:42:39,583 --> 00:42:41,667
[faint distant chatter]

670
00:43:06,333 --> 00:43:07,958
[footsteps approaching]

671
00:43:08,583 --> 00:43:09,583
[Rit] Ah…

672
00:43:12,333 --> 00:43:13,792
[bell tolling in distance]

673
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:31,250
How have you been?

674
00:43:31,333 --> 00:43:33,000
You took an early retirement.

675
00:43:38,042 --> 00:43:39,125
It's a good thing.

676
00:43:40,417 --> 00:43:42,833
I have more time to do what I want to do.

677
00:43:45,958 --> 00:43:46,917
[Rit sighs]

678
00:43:47,542 --> 00:43:49,917
Your mom must be glad you came.

679
00:43:53,958 --> 00:43:55,667
I wanted to come see her first,

680
00:43:56,250 --> 00:43:58,208
in case I can't visit for a while.

681
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:05,958
If you really have to go to prison,

682
00:44:07,625 --> 00:44:09,458
I'd be heartbroken.

683
00:44:14,667 --> 00:44:17,208
The system I've trusted my whole life…

684
00:44:21,125 --> 00:44:24,167
can't even get justice for my own son.

685
00:44:25,208 --> 00:44:28,000
[soft pensive music playing]

686
00:44:51,125 --> 00:44:52,208
[Rit sighs]

687
00:44:54,958 --> 00:44:57,292
[woman in Burmese] The fish…
you can just leave it there.

688
00:44:57,375 --> 00:44:58,375
Where exactly?

689
00:44:58,458 --> 00:45:00,875
- Right there.
- Okay.

690
00:45:00,958 --> 00:45:03,500
- [in Thai] Is this all Pang left behind?
- Yes.

691
00:45:03,583 --> 00:45:05,583
[soft pensive music continues]

692
00:45:05,667 --> 00:45:07,042
[footsteps approaching]

693
00:45:09,458 --> 00:45:10,583
Thank you.

694
00:45:20,833 --> 00:45:23,458
- [distant chatter]
- [music concludes]

695
00:45:25,625 --> 00:45:26,750
[Ang] What is it?

696
00:45:29,292 --> 00:45:30,625
Is Seya not around?

697
00:45:40,417 --> 00:45:41,667
I just want to apologize.

698
00:45:42,625 --> 00:45:43,708
No need.

699
00:45:44,500 --> 00:45:45,833
I already explained to him.

700
00:45:56,250 --> 00:45:57,708
I really had no choice.

701
00:46:02,417 --> 00:46:03,917
You lied to save yourself.

702
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:07,083
But I risked exposing the truth,

703
00:46:08,250 --> 00:46:10,500
and it didn't change a fucking thing.

704
00:46:16,292 --> 00:46:19,542
[soft somber music playing]

705
00:46:26,625 --> 00:46:28,208
I understand it all.

706
00:46:31,625 --> 00:46:34,000
I completely get how this world works.

707
00:46:36,917 --> 00:46:39,000
But I just can't accept it.

708
00:46:40,208 --> 00:46:41,792
- [Ang sniffles]
- [papers rustling]

709
00:46:41,875 --> 00:46:44,125
[gentle guitar music overlapping]

710
00:46:49,625 --> 00:46:50,792
[Ang sniffles]

711
00:47:10,167 --> 00:47:11,875
If the court won't grant me bail…

712
00:47:20,208 --> 00:47:22,458
please check in on my dad sometimes.

713
00:47:56,458 --> 00:48:03,375
EQUAL THAI PARTY MEMBERSHIP OPEN
BUILD AN EQUAL THAILAND WITH US

714
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:10,125
I believe you can do it.

715
00:48:12,667 --> 00:48:14,500
[breathes shakily]

716
00:48:16,125 --> 00:48:17,500
[Ang sobs]

717
00:48:22,917 --> 00:48:23,875
[sniffles]

718
00:48:23,958 --> 00:48:28,333
[news anchor] <i>The search for the culprit</i>
<i>in the golf course murder case continues.</i>

719
00:48:28,417 --> 00:48:30,833
<i>Pol. Gen. Anan Methaneepaisal</i>

720
00:48:30,917 --> 00:48:35,458
<i>has stated that he was denied justice</i>
<i>and the evidence was distorted</i>

721
00:48:35,542 --> 00:48:37,792
<i>in his own son's murder case.</i>

722
00:48:37,875 --> 00:48:40,583
- [soft pensive music playing]
<i>- Let's listen to his statement.</i>

723
00:48:40,667 --> 00:48:43,125
<i>I maintain my innocence.</i>

724
00:48:43,208 --> 00:48:45,708
<i>I've faced many ill-wishers in my life,</i>

725
00:48:45,792 --> 00:48:47,792
<i>but I always pull through.</i>

726
00:48:49,083 --> 00:48:50,417
<i>I do believe</i>

727
00:48:50,500 --> 00:48:53,292
<i>that the higher powers will protect me.</i>

728
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:02,083
[traffic honking]

729
00:49:04,625 --> 00:49:07,667
[soft pensive music continues]

730
00:49:23,708 --> 00:49:25,667
[music fades]

731
00:49:27,583 --> 00:49:30,250
MISSING PERSON

732
00:49:30,333 --> 00:49:35,500
[sentimental Thai song playing]

733
00:49:39,667 --> 00:49:45,000
[sentimental Thai song continues]

734
00:49:50,667 --> 00:49:57,333
[sentimental Thai song continues]

735
00:50:05,875 --> 00:50:10,750
[sentimental Thai song continues]

736
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:26,042
[sentimental Thai song continues]

737
00:50:28,583 --> 00:50:33,458
[sentimental Thai song continues]

738
00:50:38,208 --> 00:50:42,875
[sentimental Thai song continues]

739
00:50:49,417 --> 00:50:53,083
[sentimental Thai song continues]

740
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:02,458
[sentimental Thai song continues]

741
00:51:04,708 --> 00:51:07,542
[sentimental Thai song continues]

742
00:51:14,083 --> 00:51:16,458
[sentimental Thai song continues]

743
00:51:16,542 --> 00:51:17,875
DR. KORN CASE

744
00:51:27,333 --> 00:51:31,375
[sentimental Thai song continues]

745
00:51:45,750 --> 00:51:49,042
EQUAL THAI PARTY

746
00:51:49,125 --> 00:51:52,792
[sentimental Thai song continues]

747
00:52:01,375 --> 00:52:04,333
[sentimental Thai song continues]

748
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:20,500
[sentimental Thai song continues]

749
00:52:35,875 --> 00:52:39,125
[sentimental Thai song continues]

750
00:52:54,333 --> 00:52:57,750
[sentimental Thai song continues]

751
00:53:21,458 --> 00:53:23,875
[song concludes]

752
00:53:25,583 --> 00:53:29,167
THE DAY OF THE VERDICT

753
00:53:52,875 --> 00:53:58,667
The verdict for case no. O.927/2568.

754
00:53:59,417 --> 00:54:04,542
The prosecution alleges that
on October 14, 2025,

755
00:54:04,625 --> 00:54:05,875
during the night,

756
00:54:05,958 --> 00:54:09,542
the defendant struck the victim's head
multiple times with a golf club,

757
00:54:09,625 --> 00:54:12,542
causing the victim to fall and die.

758
00:54:12,625 --> 00:54:15,750
The prosecution cited eyewitnesses
who claim to have seen the defendant

759
00:54:15,833 --> 00:54:17,708
holding a golf club at the scene.

760
00:54:17,792 --> 00:54:19,417
Circumstantial evidence
was also presented.

761
00:54:19,500 --> 00:54:22,292
The defendant denied all charges,

762
00:54:22,375 --> 00:54:24,417
claiming that on the day of the incident,

763
00:54:24,500 --> 00:54:27,000
the victim threatened him with a gun

764
00:54:27,083 --> 00:54:30,583
to silence Ms. Nay Oo, a Myanmar national.

765
00:54:30,667 --> 00:54:33,875
But the defendant retracted his statement

766
00:54:33,958 --> 00:54:37,917
admitting to conspiring with the deceased

767
00:54:38,000 --> 00:54:40,417
to silence Ms. Nay Oo.

768
00:54:41,042 --> 00:54:43,750
Upon reviewing the charges
and testimonies,

769
00:54:43,833 --> 00:54:46,542
the prosecution's evidence

770
00:54:46,625 --> 00:54:49,167
leaves room for reasonable doubt.

771
00:54:49,250 --> 00:54:53,375
The missing gun that was later found.

772
00:54:53,458 --> 00:54:56,125
According to
Mr. Sorn Saengruangnop's testimony,

773
00:54:56,208 --> 00:54:57,917
he claimed to hear gunshots.

774
00:54:58,000 --> 00:55:01,917
Forensic evidence also indicates
that the gun found

775
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:04,417
is linked to both the victim
and the defendant.

776
00:55:04,500 --> 00:55:06,292
However, the prosecution's presentation

777
00:55:06,375 --> 00:55:08,875
makes no mention of the gun at the scene.

778
00:55:08,958 --> 00:55:13,500
This casts doubt on
how evidence was obtained.

779
00:55:14,125 --> 00:55:17,667
There is reasonable doubt in the evidence.

780
00:55:17,750 --> 00:55:20,083
The defendant cannot be sentenced.

781
00:55:21,333 --> 00:55:25,125
The court gives the defendant
the benefit of the doubt,

782
00:55:25,208 --> 00:55:30,417
under Section 227 Paragraph 2
of the Procedure Code.

783
00:55:30,500 --> 00:55:33,667
- [crowd chattering]
- [mellow guitar music playing]

784
00:55:39,708 --> 00:55:40,875
[Kung] See that?

785
00:55:41,667 --> 00:55:42,792
You see that?

786
00:55:44,542 --> 00:55:46,833
I told you, fucker! You're a good man.

787
00:55:46,917 --> 00:55:47,917
Fuck yeah!

788
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:49,208
My brother is a good man!

789
00:55:49,292 --> 00:55:51,250
He's a good man. [laughs]

790
00:55:54,083 --> 00:55:55,417
My brother is a good man!

791
00:55:57,042 --> 00:55:58,917
Sir, your son is a good man.

792
00:55:59,417 --> 00:56:00,667
See you at home.

793
00:56:07,542 --> 00:56:10,125
[Kung] You're an innocent man, fucker!

794
00:56:11,833 --> 00:56:15,208
Walking tall like a free man,

795
00:56:15,292 --> 00:56:17,583
leaving the respected court,

796
00:56:17,667 --> 00:56:19,792
the once dark clouds

797
00:56:19,875 --> 00:56:24,208
are now proven clear and bright.

798
00:56:24,292 --> 00:56:27,375
- [laughs]
- Hey, it's Mek, the free man!

799
00:56:27,458 --> 00:56:29,000
- Welcome back, bro.
- [music concludes]

800
00:56:29,083 --> 00:56:31,792
Hold on, I'm streaming this for my mom.

801
00:56:31,875 --> 00:56:32,917
- Look.
- Hey, Nemo.

802
00:56:33,000 --> 00:56:34,917
- Yeah?
- Know how pissed I am right now?

803
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:36,958
- No idea.
- You don't?

804
00:56:37,042 --> 00:56:38,750
Maybe I should show you.

805
00:56:38,833 --> 00:56:41,958
I told you to stay and light the grill.

806
00:56:42,042 --> 00:56:44,208
- Why are you here?
- It was Meuk!

807
00:56:44,292 --> 00:56:46,333
He wanted to capture the vibe here.

808
00:56:46,417 --> 00:56:47,833
I just followed him.

809
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:50,417
Yeah, it's on him.

810
00:56:51,375 --> 00:56:54,167
Mek is so cool and innocent.

811
00:56:54,250 --> 00:56:56,917
Yeah, as innocent as a baby, fucker.

812
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:59,500
Come on. Let's head back!

813
00:56:59,583 --> 00:57:01,750
Lead the hero.

814
00:57:01,833 --> 00:57:03,583
Back to our homeland.

815
00:57:03,667 --> 00:57:05,958
- Yeah! [laughs]
- [Nemo] Let's go!

816
00:57:06,042 --> 00:57:09,958
Thai BBQ tonight! Thin sliced pork.

817
00:57:10,042 --> 00:57:11,125
See you soon.

818
00:57:12,458 --> 00:57:14,875
[Kung] We are having BBQ pork tonight.

819
00:57:17,000 --> 00:57:18,417
Aren't you happy?

820
00:57:24,250 --> 00:57:25,500
[sighs]

821
00:57:27,750 --> 00:57:29,250
I tried so hard

822
00:57:30,250 --> 00:57:33,167
to prove my innocence.

823
00:57:35,000 --> 00:57:37,708
But in the end, I lied that I did it,

824
00:57:39,167 --> 00:57:40,167
and I walked free.

825
00:57:42,917 --> 00:57:44,167
You'll get used to it.

826
00:57:46,250 --> 00:57:49,792
- [birds chirping]
- [soft uplifting music playing]

827
00:57:55,375 --> 00:57:56,667
What is this?

828
00:57:56,750 --> 00:57:58,708
Anan's victims forming a team?

829
00:58:00,208 --> 00:58:01,458
I hate the team name.

830
00:58:05,833 --> 00:58:08,375
[music turns upbeat]

831
00:58:09,750 --> 00:58:12,333
And I hope we never see each other again.

832
00:58:16,667 --> 00:58:17,958
Wait a minute.

833
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:23,458
Someone wants to see you.

834
00:58:36,458 --> 00:58:38,125
[music fades]

835
00:58:39,292 --> 00:58:42,917
[intriguing guitar music playing]

836
00:58:59,958 --> 00:59:01,375
- [music fades]
- Don't worry.

837
00:59:01,458 --> 00:59:03,375
Anan wouldn't dare do anything to you.

838
00:59:04,750 --> 00:59:06,500
I still have a bad feeling about this.

839
00:59:06,583 --> 00:59:10,625
Even if Anan is trying to beat
the trafficking charge on appeal,

840
00:59:10,708 --> 00:59:13,042
why does he need to talk to us now?

841
00:59:21,167 --> 00:59:24,167
A drowning man will clutch at any straw.

842
00:59:59,458 --> 01:00:01,083
[man] Have a seat, Jittri.

843
01:00:04,958 --> 01:00:06,000
Mek.

844
01:00:07,667 --> 01:00:10,417
[ominous music playing]

845
01:00:17,250 --> 01:00:18,833
Why did you bring them here?

846
01:00:19,583 --> 01:00:22,042
[man] Calm down, Anan. Hear me out.

847
01:00:23,542 --> 01:00:27,000
The situation is
you've humiliated our investors.

848
01:00:27,083 --> 01:00:29,042
You got their guy deported.

849
01:00:29,708 --> 01:00:32,375
The higher-ups aren't happy.
You should know that.

850
01:00:35,750 --> 01:00:39,375
I invited everyone here today
because I need some advice.

851
01:00:41,417 --> 01:00:43,667
All of this has been approved by…

852
01:00:45,250 --> 01:00:46,625
your father-in-law.

853
01:00:46,708 --> 01:00:48,958
[dark intriguing music playing]

854
01:00:51,542 --> 01:00:54,375
[man] I want you attorneys to brainstorm.

855
01:00:56,042 --> 01:00:57,542
[music fades]

856
01:00:57,625 --> 01:01:00,708
How should we explain
Anan's cause of death?

857
01:01:00,792 --> 01:01:04,542
[dark tense music playing]

858
01:01:04,625 --> 01:01:06,875
[breathes shakily]

859
01:01:08,292 --> 01:01:10,375
He shot himself to escape the stress

860
01:01:10,458 --> 01:01:12,208
because of the trafficking charge.

861
01:01:13,542 --> 01:01:15,083
Is that too cliché?

862
01:01:16,433 --> 01:01:17,542
[grunts]

863
01:01:17,625 --> 01:01:19,125
- No!
- [gunshot]

864
01:01:19,208 --> 01:01:21,083
- [Jittri sobs]
- [music intensifies]

865
01:01:25,250 --> 01:01:30,458
Or he shot himself because
he was caught dating his police aide.

866
01:01:31,875 --> 01:01:33,833
He was afraid to shame his father-in-law.

867
01:01:35,292 --> 01:01:37,917
We'll let the maid find the body first.

868
01:01:38,583 --> 01:01:40,208
The gun belongs to Anan himself.

869
01:01:43,125 --> 01:01:44,125
Hmm…

870
01:01:45,083 --> 01:01:46,542
Are we missing anything else?

871
01:01:48,833 --> 01:01:50,250
[music falls]

872
01:01:50,333 --> 01:01:51,708
What do you two think?

873
01:01:52,833 --> 01:01:55,833
[sobbing]

874
01:02:04,625 --> 01:02:06,792
- Do your job, Jittri.
- [sobs heavily]

875
01:02:12,833 --> 01:02:13,750
[gulps]

876
01:02:13,833 --> 01:02:16,167
The police… What about the police aide?

877
01:02:18,958 --> 01:02:20,333
Already taken care of.

878
01:02:21,458 --> 01:02:23,292
I used this exact same gun.

879
01:02:23,375 --> 01:02:24,375
[in English] Okay.

880
01:02:26,208 --> 01:02:29,208
[in Thai] They were caught,
and both were ashamed.

881
01:02:31,250 --> 01:02:32,375
They couldn't take it.

882
01:02:34,542 --> 01:02:35,625
Case closed.

883
01:02:35,708 --> 01:02:38,167
[sinister music playing]

884
01:02:38,250 --> 01:02:41,125
[Mek breathes shakily]

885
01:02:48,417 --> 01:02:49,917
You've grown up a lot, Mek.

886
01:02:52,625 --> 01:02:53,875
How's your dad doing?

887
01:02:53,958 --> 01:02:55,750
[music rises]

888
01:02:58,500 --> 01:03:00,583
[music falls]

889
01:03:04,500 --> 01:03:07,250
[dark dramatic music playing]

890
01:03:14,042 --> 01:03:15,750
[Wimol] It's okay, Mek.

891
01:03:15,833 --> 01:03:17,500
[young Mek whimpers]

892
01:03:20,083 --> 01:03:21,292
Help!

893
01:03:33,167 --> 01:03:34,458
Don't you remember me?

894
01:03:34,542 --> 01:03:35,792
[music falls]

895
01:03:38,292 --> 01:03:39,583
I'm Kosol,

896
01:03:40,333 --> 01:03:41,792
the man who had your mother killed.

897
01:03:41,875 --> 01:03:44,125
[music rises, intensifies]

898
01:03:45,542 --> 01:03:46,708
This is Jittri.

899
01:03:47,750 --> 01:03:48,750
She's my lawyer.

900
01:04:03,667 --> 01:04:06,125
[music builds]

901
01:04:06,208 --> 01:04:12,625
[music concludes]

902
01:04:17,458 --> 01:04:21,375
[soft organ music playing]

903
01:04:29,458 --> 01:04:33,375
[sentimental Thai rock song playing]

904
01:05:03,292 --> 01:05:10,083
[sentimental Thai rock song continues]

905
01:05:33,542 --> 01:05:40,083
[sentimental Thai rock song continues]

906
01:06:13,417 --> 01:06:19,583
[sentimental Thai rock song continues]

907
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:46,417
[song concludes]
